The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional networks for terrain safety segmentation on autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves semantic segmentation using a single camera, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the real-time operation of the system, which suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of the system for navigation on an indoor robot suggests systems and control (cs.SY) as a possible sub-category.
